Heart Rate Variability: variance in time between heartbeats. measured in ms
CSF Tau Concentrations: Concentration of the Tau protein in cerebrospinal fluid. measured in pg/mL
Unconsciousness Duration Upon Injury: How long a person is in an unresponsive state after an injury. measured in hours.
Head Injury Type: a head injury can either be open, where a victim suffers from damage to their brain and skull or bone structure, or closed, where there is no damage to the skull or bone structure, but rather internal brain bleeding
Time Since Injury: time that has elapsed since the impact to the head. measured in minutes.
Arm Injury Severity: arm pain that ranges from manageable to severe measured by asking the patient. external signs to arm injury include bleeding, protruding bone, or deformity measured by visible injury
Acne Severity: can be classified by number of eruptions on the skin. the more eruptions, the more severe. can also be classified by the type of acne, which ranges from inflammatory lesions to inflamatory lesions to nodules and scarring. measured by count and type of eruption.
Day to Day Happiness and Satisfaction: how happy and satisfied one is with their life. measured on a scale from 1-5 where 1 is very unsatisfied and sad and 5 is very satisfied and happy.
Disability Rating Score: range of how much the disability affects quality of life. measured on a scale from 1-10 where 1 is minimal effect and 10 is highest level of effect on quality of life and shortens life expectancy
Obesity Rating (How Obese is the Person): how body fat is distributed and how much of someone's body is body fat measured by BMI. Range [1-3] where each number is associated to the obesity class that based on which range the BMI falls under

Heart Rate Variability: The amount of time between heart beats measured by ms between heartbeats.
CSF Tau Concentrations: Amount of Tau detected in CSF measured by picograms per ml.
Unconsciousness Duration Upon Injury: how long a person is in an unresponsive state or coma measured in days.
Head Injury Type: can range from external skull injury to internal brain injury or both. types include concussion, contusion, Intracranial hematoma, and skull fractures. measured by the Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) score
Time Since Injury: how long it has beensince the initial head impact
Arm Injury Severity: combination of how impacted or deformed the arm is externally, how painful it is for the patient, and how much mobility is lost. measured by trauma scoring scale [1-5] based on severity
Acne Severity: combination of type of acne (whiteheads, blackheads, pauples, pustles, nodules, cysts) and how many eruptions there are measured by scale from [1-4] in increasing severity.
Day to Day Happiness and Satisfaction: how happy or satisfied someone is with their actions, surroundings, and life. Range: [1-10] by increasing happiness
Disability Rating Score: how impactful the disability is on quality of life and life expectancy. Measured on Kurtzke Expanded Disability Status Scale (EDSS). Range: [0 to 10]
Obesity Rating (How Obese is the Person): If your BMI is 18.5 to <25, it falls within the healthy weight range. If your BMI is 25.0 to <30, it falls within the overweight range. If your BMI is 30.0 or higher, it falls within the obesity range.

Heart Rate Variability: The standard deviation of all NN intervals within a 5 minute period taken using an electrocardiogram (EKG). Units in ms.
CSF Tau Concentrations: The concentration of Tau Filament in the cerebral spinal fluid, pulled with a lumbar puncture. Measured in micro-Molarity.
Unconsciousness Duration Upon Injury: How long the patient is unconscious upon impact and receiving the injury. Longer unconsciousness indicates a more severe case of TBI. Measured in minutes.
Head Injury Type: The location where the head injury occurred. Either front, left side, right side, back, or on top. specifically the location of impact. Location 1-4 moving around the head, and 0 for on top.
Time Since Injury: The number of days that have elapsed since receiving the injury.
Arm Injury Severity: A measure of how severe an arm injury is range 0-5. With 0 as no difference with the arm usability, and 5 as the need to completely immobilize in a cast.
Acne Severity: A measure of the severity of the facial acne [1-3]. 1 is mild or no visible acne. 2 is apparent and problematic acne. 3 is severe acne leading to scarring.
Day to Day Happiness and Satisfaction: A survey response for 10 questions on the patient's overall happiness and satisfaction in work and personal life. Responses were recorded between 1-6, with 1 being little satisfaction and extreme unhappiness, and 6 being well satisfied and happy.
Disability Rating Score: A survey of the disability rating from the caregiver of the patient. The result is an average of 20 questions about the patient's ability to carry out day-to-day activities.
Obesity Rating (How Obese is the Person): An obesity rating based on the BMI range of the patient. Also weights in past prescriptions for obesity and progress current management strategies.

Heart Rate Variability: The mean variance of the heart rate space, measured in ms. Averaged through and entire EKG taken at the hospital bed.
CSF Tau Concentrations: Tau Filament is measured by taking a sample of the CSF within 24 hours of admitting using a BioGen Tau Assay.
Unconsciousness Duration Upon Injury: Length of time that the patient was unconscious following the injury. If the patient was never unconscious, this is counted as 0 minutes. Time recorded in minutes.
Head Injury Type: The classification of the head injury based on the location. 0 for hard skull, 1 for soft skull, 2 for critical areas (such as the temple).
Time Since Injury: How long, in hours, that have passed since the initial injury.
Arm Injury Severity: A measurement of the arm injury severity. Scaling with the expected time of recovery for the arm injury.
Acne Severity: How severe the patient's acne appears. 1-10 for the number of pimples or rashes across the face and chest.
Day to Day Happiness and Satisfaction: A patient's indication 1-10 of their day to day happiness and satisfaction.
Disability Rating Score: Indicator for prior disabilities that the patient had. Mark 1 if any disabilities were noted medically.
Obesity Rating (How Obese is the Person): An indicator for prior history in the medical record if the patient was obese, morbidly obese, or diagnosed overweight.

Heart Rate Variability: HRV is a measure of the variability in time between heart beats in milliseconds. Measured using a pulse oximeter. Low variability Predicts higher stress.
CSF Tau Concentrations: A bio marker for neurological disorder such as Alzheimer disease. Measures the amount of protein in cerebral spinal fluid. Measured pg/ml
Unconsciousness Duration Upon Injury: Loss of consciousness for a given amount of time to indicate brain injury
Head Injury Type: Level of brain trauma or injury. Measured by defined levels. 1-5
Time Since Injury: The amount of time needed to recover from a concussion
Arm Injury Severity: Type of arm injury. Listed condition and severity
Acne Severity: Acne Measured by grade 1-4. Count types of lesion and scratches, frequency and location.
Day to Day Happiness and Satisfaction: Self reported on a scale 1-10. Questions about daily tasks and engagement if desired activities or changes in activity level
Disability Rating Score: DRS is a percentage of your disability. 0% is someone with no disability. Used to determine qualifications for workman compensation
Obesity Rating (How Obese is the Person): Body mass index (BMI) is a person's weight in kilograms divided by the square of height in meters.
